"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "1655: numbers, hundreds and thousands",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1655",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The words “hundreds” and, especially, “thousands”, often refer to large quantities in general; they are also used simply in a superlative sense.</p>\n<h2>Hundreds</h2>\n<h3>A hundred in Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:23\">MAT 13:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:20\">MRK 4:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:8\">MAT 13:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:8\">MRK 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:8\">LUK 8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12\">MAT 18:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:4\">LUK 15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:28\">MAT 18:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:30\">MRK 10:30</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham becomes a father at 100</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:17\">GEN 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:5\">GEN 21:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:19\">ROM 4:19</a></p>\n<h3>People who lived to over 100</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:3-Gen5:32\">GEN 5:3–5:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:29\">GEN 9:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:10-Gen11:32\">GEN 11:10–11:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:7\">GEN 25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:17\">GEN 25:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:22\">GEN 50:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:7\">DEU 34:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:8\">JDG 2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:15\">2CH 24:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:16\">JOB 42:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:20\">ISA 65:20</a></p>\n<h2>Hundreds and thousands</h2>\n<h3>Hundreds and thousands as military units</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:21\">EXO 18:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:14\">NUM 31:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:7\">1SA 22:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:1\">2SA 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:1\">1CH 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:1\">1CH 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:1\">1CH 28:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:5\">2CH 25:5</a></p>\n<h3>Hundreds and thousands in blessings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:11\">DEU 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:60\">GEN 24:60</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:3\">2SA 24:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:3\">1CH 21:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:13\">PSA 144:13</a></p>\n<h2>Thousands</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ feeds thousands</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:21\">MAT 14:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:44\">MRK 6:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:14\">LUK 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:10\">JHN 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:38\">MAT 15:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:9\">MRK 8:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:9-Matt16:10\">MAT 16:9–16:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:19-Mark8:20\">MRK 8:19–8:20</a></p>\n<h3>Believers numbered in thousands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:20\">ACT 21:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41\">ACT 2:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:4\">ACT 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:4\">ROM 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:18\">1KI 19:18</a></p>\n<h3>God shows his love to thousands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:6–34:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:6\">EXO 20:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:10\">DEU 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:9\">DEU 7:9</a></p>\n<h3>God has thousands of attendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:11\">REV 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:17\">PSA 68:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:10\">DAN 7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22\">HEB 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:14\">JUD 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>God protects one believer amidst thousands of people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:7\">PSA 91:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God helps one believer against a thousand</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:10\">JOS 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:15-Judg15:16\">JDG 15:15–15:16</a></p>\n<h3>God allows thousands to be defeated</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:30\">DEU 32:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:17\">ISA 30:17</a></p>\n<h3>A thousand years</h3>\n<p>As a day to the Lord:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:4\">PSA 90:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:8\">2PE 3:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2-Rev20:7\">REV 20:2–20:7</a> <em>the reign of Jesus Christ with believers for 1,000 years while Satan is restrained</em></p>\n<h2>Special numbers</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:18\">REV 13:18</a> <em>666 is a symbol of total incompleteness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:4\">REV 7:4</a> <em>144,000 symbolises the perfect number of God's people.</em></p>\n<h2>God's people are without number</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:10\">GEN 16:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:36\">NUM 10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's people are compared to stars and sand</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:17\">GEN 22:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:5\">GEN 15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13\">EXO 32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:22\">DEU 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:23\">1CH 27:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:23\">NEH 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:22\">JER 33:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:12\">HEB 11:12</a></p>",
